###########################################################################################
FILES: adm0_centroids.tsv and adm1_centroids.tsv ###########################################################################################

What: latitude, longitude and population of all admin0 and admin1 units in Africa

Data sources:  
		shared by: Wes Hinsley on 24 May 2017

I’ve rasterised the latest GADM shapes to ADM0 and ADM1 level, then mashed those with Landscan 2015, and found the population-weighted centroid of each adm1 or adm0 unit, which will be a longitude/latitude pair within the cell where the centroid is, assuming uniform dispersion of people inside that landscan cell. I’ve given the population of each shape too.

